igital advertising. Annual revenue has surpassed $60 billion, and the platform has maintained its position as the #1 streaming platform in the U.S. for nearly three consecutive years.\n\nThe company\u2019s subscription ecosystem is also accelerating, with 350 million paid subscriptions, driven by offerings such as YouTube Premium, Google One, and the Gemini AI platform. Gemini Enterprise paid MAUs grew +40% QoQ, while generative AI cloud revenue surged +800% YoY, reinforcing Alphabet\u2019s full-stack leadership in AI.\n\nAI integration across products continues to drive engagement. AI-powered tools supported over 1 million channels daily, while features like Ask (used by ~20 million users) enhance user interaction. Also, AI Overviews now reach more than 2 billion monthly users across 200+ countries, increasing query volume by around 10% in supported categories.\n\nGoogle Cloud is another major growth driver, with backlog nearly doubling QoQ to $460 billion and expected to grow 50% over the next 24 months, fueled by enterprise and public-sector AI adoption.\n\nDespite aggressive AI investment, Alphabet maintains exceptional cash generation, allowing it to fund innovation while preserving strong profitability, making it one of the few companies capable of combining scale, growth, and financial resilience.", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 31, "replyCount": 9, "likeCount": 293, "quoteCount": 3, "viewCount": 86005, "createdAt": "Sat May 02 13:29:12 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 195, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2050568289290445186", "displayTextRange": [0, 280], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "BourbonCap", "url": "https://x.com/BourbonCap", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/BourbonCap", "id": "251912158", "name": "Bourbon Capital", "isVerified": false, "isBlueVerified": true, "verifiedType": null, "profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_image